video_name: 🥪Mechadito Ingredientes: 1kg de Roast Beef 1 Morron 1 Cebolla 2 dientes de ajo 1 Puñado de sal 1 Lata de Tomate Agua Lo dejas cocinando por minimo 2 horas. Cuanto mas lo dejes, mas se va a desarmar. Podes cortar la carne en pedazos mas chicos para que se haga mas rapido. Para hacer el sandwich ahuecas un pan. Le pones queso arriba y orégano. Lo derretis un poco en el horno y listo! #fyp #recipesoftiktok #recetasfaciles #receta

bio: No es otra pagina de recetas más.
video_name: Matambrito de Cerdo al Verdeo con Papas Españolas La primer comida que recuerdo 500gr Matambrito de Cerdo 2 Cebollas de verdeo 200ml de Crema 2 Papas Aceite y Sal El matmbrito lo cocinas desde la sarten fria a fuego medio/bajo. No se va a secar porque tiene una buena cantidad de grasa y al mismo tiempo se va a dorar. La crema es solamente calentarla un poco, no la cocines demasiado. Evita que empiecen a salir muchas burbujas. Y las papas yo la tire asi nomas. Sin pasar por agua ni nada, con el aceite a temperatura media deberian ir dorandose y quedar crocantes. Revolvelas un poco para que no se peguen. #receta #recetasfaciles #recipesoftiktok #fyp

bio: No es otra pagina de recetas más.
video_name: Este Pollo viene con Sorpresa Ingredientes: 1.5kg de Pollo (Pata y muslo) 2 Tazas de Harina de trigo 1/2 Taza de Fecula de maiz 2 Cucharaditas de Polvo de hornear Especias: (Podes poner lo que quieras) 2 Cucharadas de sal 1 Cucharada de Ajo en polvo 1 Cucharada de Pimenton 1 Cucharada de Tomillo 1 Cucharada de Pimienta 2 Huevos 100ml de Agua (Es medio a ojo) Para la salsa: Perejil 1/2 cebolla 1/2 diente de ajo 1 cebolla de verdeo 2 Cucharadas de Mayonesa 4 Cucharas de Yogur Neutro Sal y Pimienta Jugo de Medio limon Freir en aceite a 160°C 18 minutos y dejar enfriar. (Tarda en bajar la temperatura, asi que se sigue cocinando y se va poniendo mas crocante) Es importante que haya bastante aceite y no pongas mucho pollo porque sino lo vas a enfriar demasiado. Masomenos por 1lt de aceite mete 3/4 piezas Podes usar el truco de la cucharada de madera para medir la temperatura O si lo pones a fuego medio y precalentas por 15 minutos va estar bien. #fyp #recipesoftiktok #recetasfaciles #receta

bio: No es otra pagina de recetas más.
video_name: Ramen Un par de aclaraciones previas.  El ramen es una comida que lleva tiempo, hay muchas versiones pero todas tienen como protagonistas caldos que llevan mucha coccion. Esta es una version rapida porque a mi tampoco me tienta la idea de estar 3 dias para hacer unos fideos. Ingredientes:  1kg de Cerdo (Usé Bondiola) Huevo duro Hongos (Usé champigniones, lo ideal es shitake pero no se consiguen facil) Fideos  Verdeo crudo picado Para el Caldo: Doras la carne 6 Dientes de Ajo 1 Jengibre 1 Cebolla de verdeo 1 Puerro 1 Cebolla 1/2 Taza de Azucar 1 Taza de Salsa de Soja Lo tapas con agua (Minimo 1,5 lt agrega) Dejas hervir a fuego bajo por 1 hora y media. Despues colas el caldo y metes lo hongos a remojar ahi mientras cortas la carne y preparas los fideos. Las cosas clave: Si el caldo te quedo muy fuerte (se redujo mucho) podes agregarle agua o al momento de servir en el plato una cucharada del agua de los fideos. Y si usaste el polvo saborizante que viene de los fideos ramen comprados todavia mejor. Para que los huevos queden así. Los pones al fuego con agua fria y en cuanto hierve con ganas contas 6 minutos exacto. Los sacas y rapido en agua helada. La idea de atar la carne es para que no pierda la forma circular. #receta #recetasfaciles #recipesoftiktok #fyp

video_name: Asi es El Verdadero Goulash Ingredientes para 4: 1kg de Carne  2 Cebollas  4 Cucharadas de Paprika 1 Cucharada de Semillas de Kummel 1/2 Morron 1 Tomate 800gr de Papa Caldo/agua y Sal Para lo Csipetke: 1 huevo 200gr de Harina Sal Haces la masa, la pellizcas y los tiras 5 minutos a cocinar Claves: Es importante ir mirando el goulash para que no se quede sin agua. Al tener papa no es necesario hacer tanto csipetke Usa una olla grande, sino va a desbordar. Claramente podes reemplazar la paprika por pimenton y el kummel por hinojo si no conseguis. Desde que tiras la papa son aprox. 30 minutos mas. Lo importante es que lo pruebes. #receta #recetasfaciles #recipesoftiktok #fyp

video_name: nutella stuffed chocolate chip cookies !    recipe:   1/2 cup butter, browned (113g) 1/4 cup granulated sugar (50g) 1/2 cup dark brown sugar, packed (100g) 1 large egg  1 tsp vanilla extract (5g) 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour (190g) 1/2 tsp baking soda (3g) 1/4 tsp salt (1g) chocolate chips(measure with your heart idk, i used @Nestle Toll House ) 6 tbsp nutella(90g)(i used 3 for the cookies & the rest to drizzle.)  instructions- brown the butter & let cool slightly. in a bowl whisk together the browned butter & sugars until glossy. add the egg & vanilla and mix until combined. add in the flour, baking soda, and salt and fold gently then add chocolate chips and fold until the dough comes together. scoop dough balls, flatten slightly, place a frozen nutella scoop in the center, and roll it back up. bake at 350°f (175°c) for 11–13 minutes until golden on the edges but soft in the middle.( i made 3 big cookies & 6 small ones. the bigger ones cooked for 15-17 minutes. )    #nutella #chocolatechipcookies #cookies #fyp #baking

video_name: salted caramel brownies !! also thank you sm for 200k 💞      here’s the recipe:   1/2 cup brown butter(113g) 1/2 cup granulated sugar(100g) 1/2 cup brown sugar(100g) 2 eggs 1/2 tsp vanilla(2g) 1/2 cup flour(60g) 1/2 cup cocoa powder(45g) 1/2 cup choc chips(85g)( split to add some in batter and some in butter )( i used dark choc if you use semi or milk your brownies will be sweeter so i reccomend adjusting the sugar 2-3 tbsp. )( i used @Nestle Toll House )  1/4 tsp salt(1.5g) 1/4 tsp baking soda(1g) 1 tsp instant coffee ( i used @NESCAFÉ USA ) brown your butter and add in the chocolate chips while it’s still warm. melt the chocolate and add in both sugars. ( make sure it’s still warm to melt it a bit ) mix well then add in your eggs. mix until it gets thick & glossy. sift in your dry ingredients & chocolate chips and fold everything together. bake at 350•F for about 25 minutes. let it cool and then drizzle caramel.    quick & easy salted caramel recipe:   1/2 cup brown sugar(100g) 1/4 cup butter(56g) 1/4 cup heavy cream(60g)  1/4 tsp salt ( adjust to taste )(3g)   add your sugar & butter to a pan and let it melt continue to mix so it doesn’t burn. once it’s bubbling slowly add in heavy cream, it’ll bubble a bit but keep mixing. take it off heat and add salt then let it cool.  #brownie #recipe #baking #fyp #fudgybrownies

video_name: chocolate nutella cinnamon rolls 🤎 these tasted like chocolate donuts ??    recipe:   3/4 cup warm milk(180g) 3 tbsp melted butter(43g) 4 tbsp granulated sugar(50g) 2 1/4 tsp yeast(7g) 1 egg 1 yolk 3 cups of flour(360g) 3 tbsp cocoa powder(18g) 1/4 tsp salt(1.5g) 1/4 cup heavy cream(60g) ( goes on top before baking )    mix your warm milk. sugar, and yeast and let sit for 5-10 minutes. once frothy add in your egg and butter and mix. then add in your dry ingredients and continue mixing until it becomes a shaggy dough. knead until a smooth dough forms. ( you may need to add a bit more flour. but i reccomend coating your hands in olive oil and kneading that way. ) let sit in an oiled bowl covered for 1 hr. after the hour punch the dough down and roll it out.    filling:   1/4 cup melted butter(57g)  1 cup brown sugar(200g) 3 tsp cinnamon(7-8g) 2-3 tbsp nutella (40-60g) 1 tbsp cocoa powder(6g)   mix until combined. let your butter cool a tad bit just so it doesn’t melt the sugar. spread over rolled out dough & roll them up. cut your desired cinnamon roll sizes & let sit for another 30 minutes. pour heavy cream over top of rolls and bake at 350•F for about 25-35 minutes. ( can vary depending on your oven ) while they’re still warm spread nutella over top. or use a different frosting recipe( i didn’t like the idea of chocolate cream cheese frosting idk )    #chocolate #cinnamonroll #nutella #bakingrecipe #fyp

video_name: fudgy brownies 🤎    easy recipe:   1/2 cup melted butter(113g) 4 oz dark chocolate(or semi sweet it’ll just have a different look & taste)(113g) 1/2 cup granulated sugar (100g) 1/4 cup brown sugar (50g) 2 eggs 1 tsp vanilla (5ml) 1/2 cup flour (60g) 1/4 cup cocoa powder(25g) 1/4 tsp salt (1.5g) & chocolate chips    melt the butter and dark chocolate together until smooth. while it’s still warm (not hot), whisk in both sugars until combined — this helps dissolve them and gives you that shiny top later. add the eggs one at a time, mixing well after each. then mix in the vanilla. sift in the flour, cocoa powder( i added it to my chocolate mixture in the beginning), and salt, then gently fold until just combined (don’t overmix). fold in chocolate chips. bake at 325°f for 24–28 min — start checking at 20-22. a toothpick should come out with moist crumbs, not clean. enjoy :) ( i over baked mine a bit but still so good! )   #fudgybrownies #recipe #bakingtherapy #fyp #baking

video_name: the fluffiest cinnamon rolls everrr.    recipe:   dough: 3/4 cup WARM milk(180ml) 1/4 cup melted butter(57g) 1/4 cup sugar(50g) 2 1/4 tsp yeast(7g) 1 egg & 1 yolk ( rt ) 3 cups of flour(360g) 1/4 ac tsp salt(1g)   mix the warm milk with sugar & yeast and let sit for 5 mins to froth up. then add in your melted butter and eggs and mix. add your dry ingredients and knead until smooth. ( if your dough is too sticky add olive oil to your workplace & hands try not to add more flour, it keeps the dough fluffy instead of dense. )    let your dough rest covered for 1-1.5 hours, until doubled in size. roll out your dough.  filling:   1/4 cup melted butter(57g) 3/4 cup brown sugar(180g) 3 tsp cinnamon (8g)    combine everything and spread on the dough, make sure to get the edges.  roll your dough up into however many rolls you want. ( i did 8 ) let rest for another 30 mins covered. pour heavy cream over top before baking at 350•F for 20-25 minutes. ( you may need longer, also if your rolls start browning before they’re done tent with foil ) let cool before adding icing.    bottom layer : (optional) 1/4 cup soft butter(57g) 2 tbsp heavy cream(30g) 1/2 cup brown sugar(100g)   mix until combined & spread on the bottom of the pan before adding your rolls ( optional but keeps it gooey ) cream cheese frosting:   2 tbsp soft butter (room temp)(28g) 4 oz cream cheese (room temp)(113g) 1 tsp vanilla bean paste(5g) 1 cup - 1 1/2 cup powdered sugar (120-180g)   whip butter and cream cheese until fluffy, then add in your vanilla and powdered sugar, continue whipping until you have your desired consistency. if it’s too thick add heavy cream, or even maple syrup :). spread over warm(not hot) rolls and enjoy :)    #fallbaking #cinnamonroll #recipe #fyp

video_name: crispy cheesy garlic potato balls!! this time they’re super crispy :D    easy recipe:   5 yellow potatoes 5 tbsp cornstarch (plus some for rolling) (40g) 1 tsp salt (adjust to taste) (6g) 1 tsp garlic powder (3g) 1/2 tsp onion powder (1.5g) 1/4 tsp black pepper (0.5g) 1 tsp parsley (1g)   cut & peel your potatoes. then boil until they’re fork tender. add to a bowl and mash up until smooth. then add in your spices & cornstarch, mix until a dough forms. seperate your dough ( i did 1 heaping tbsp for each, i got 9 balls ) then flatten & add your cheese. roll them back up and roll in cornstarch( don’t skip this step, you want to lightly coat them it helps with the crispy skin ). let freeze for 30 mins - 1 hr. then fry until golden brown on each side. let dry on a rack a bit before eating.    #cheese #garlic #potatoes #Recipe #baking

video_name: carrot cake!! 🤎      easy recipe:   1 cup brown butter (225g) 1 cup granulated sugar (200g) 1/2 cup brown sugar (100g) 4 eggs 1/2 cup of buttermilk ( if you don’t have it mix 1 cup regular milk with 1 tbsp lemon juice or vinegar) 2 tsp vanilla 2 cups grated carrots 2 cups of flour (250g) 1 1/2 tsp baking powder(6g) 1 tsp baking soda (5g) 1 1/2 tsp cinnamon(3g) 1/2 tsp nutmeg (1g) 1/2 tsp salt(3g) preheat your oven to 350•F. whisk together the dry ingredients in one bowl. in another, mix the sugars, butter, eggs, and vanilla until smooth. combine the wet and dry, then fold in grated carrots. i made two 8x8 cakes with this recipe.    bake for 25-35 minutes. let cool before assembling the cake !    brown butter cream cheese frosting recipe:   1/2 cup butter(113g) 8 oz softened cream cheese(225g) 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar(300g) 1 1/2 tsp vanilla 1 tsp cinnamon 2 tsp maple syrup  pinch of salt    brown your butter and let it cool completely, then whip it up until fluffy beat in the cream cheese, vanilla, maple syrup & the spices. let cool until you’re ready to use .    #brownbutter #carrotcake #recipe #baking #fyp

video_name: Hungarian Goulash | Soups So Good It Can Cure Any Sickness Ep. 13 INGREDIENTS: Hungarian Goulash - 1 kg beef chuck, cut into cubes  - 1 white onion, diced  - 9-12 garlic cloves, minced  - 1/3 cup of paprika  - 1 tbsp of caraway seeds - 2 green bell peppers, chopped  - 1 red bell pepper, chopped  - 1 cup tomatoes, chopped  - Beef stock to fill the pot  - 1 potato, chopped  - 1 carrot, chopped  - Salt and pepper to taste - Oil/lard for frying  INSTRUCTIONS: - Start by seasoning your meat with salt and pepper and slice into bite sized cubes.  - In a hot soup pot sauté your garlic and onions until softened. Add your meat and season with paprika and caraway seeds. Mix until everything is combined.  - Add your chopped bell peppers along with tomatoes and mix.  - Add beef stock until the pot is filled and allow to simmer for 1-1.5 hrs minutes or until meat is tender before adding the rest of your vegetables. Season with salt and pepper. - Serve with chopped parsley and enjoy!  #Soups #asmr #ASMRCooking

video_name: 🇲🇦 Moroccan Harira | Soups So Good It Can Cure Any Sickness Ep. 15 INGREDIENTS: - 500g of lamb shoulder, cut into small cubes - Oil for frying - 1 large onion, chopped - 6-10 garlic cloves, chopped - 3 tbsp of tomato paste - 2 tsp of ginger - 1 tbsp of ground turmeric - 1 tsp of cinnamon  - 1 tsp of ground cumin - ¾ cup of chickpeas - ¾ cup brown lentils - Beef broth as needed - crushed tomatoes - 1 celery stalk (with leaves), finely chopped and cubed - 1 bunch of cilantro, chopped - 1 bunch of parsley, chopped - Flour slurry - Salt & pepper to taste - 1/2 cup broken vermicelli *all measurements are estimates. cook and season with your ❤️ INSTRUCTIONS - Heat the oil in a pot. Add in lamb and sear until browned. remove and set aside. - Stir in the onion, garlic, and add back your lamb. Add tomato paste and stir until well combined before adding celery and leaves along with the spices. - Add lentils, chickpeas, crushed tomatoes, and beef broth until the pot is full. let cook for about 40 mins or until lentils are soft. - Add your cilantro and parsley and vermicelli noodles. Season with salt and pepper. cook for about 15mins. - add your flour slurry to thicken the soup. - Serve with a squeeze of lemon and enjoy! #Soups #asmr #cookingasmr

video_name: 🇬🇷 Avgolemono | Soups So Good It Can Cure Any Sickness Ep. 14 INGREDIENTS:  Greek Avgolemono: - 5-8 chicken thigh bone in, (can also be 1 whole chicken) - Olive oil - 1 tbsp of Italian seasoning - 1 whole onion, diced - 5-10 garlic cloves, minced - 3/4 cup celery, diced - 1 carrot, diced - Chicken broth as needed - ¾ cup orzo pasta  - Bay leaves (optional) - Salt and pepper to taste Avgolemono Mixture: - 4 eggs - The juice of 2-3 lemons - lemon zesr - reserved broth from the Avgolemono Soup INSTRUCTIONS:  - Start by seasoning your chicken and searing it in a pot with a bit of oil until browned. Once golden, set the chicken aside for later. - In the same pot, sauté your vegetables until fragrant, then add Italian seasoning. add your chicken broth. - Return the chicken to the pot and set it to a gentle simmer for 45 minutes, or until tender. Once done, shred the chicken and add back to the soup. - Add the orzo pasta and let it cook in the broth for 8–10 minutes - Meanwhile, prepare the avgolemono mixture. In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs and add lemon juice/zest. To temper, pour in a thin stream a bit of hot soup while whisking constantly. This will prevent the eggs from scrambling. - Once tempered, gently stir the avgolemono mixture back into the pot. - Serve your soup hot, garnished with fresh dill/parsley and a drizzle of olive oil and enjoy! #Soups #asmr #ASMRCooking

video_name: Italian Wedding Soup | Soups So Good It Can Cure Any Sickness Ep. 12 INGREDIENTS: Meatballs: - 350g lean ground beef - 3 pcs Italian sausage, casings removed - 2 large egg - ⅓ cup of parsley, chopped - ½ tbsp of garlic powder - 2 tbsp parsley, finely chopped  - ½ cup bread crumbs - ⅓ cup grated parmesan cheese - Salt and pepper to taste Italian Wedding Soup Base: - Olive oil - 1 yellow onion, diced - 8-12 cloves of garlic, diced - 2 large carrots, diced - 2 stalks celery, diced - ½ cup of white wine - 3 cups chicken broth - 3 cups beef broth - 2 bay leaves - Salt and pepper to taste - 1 cup small pasta (orzo) - 3 cups spinach, chopped INSTRUCTIONS:  - Start by making your meatballs. Add all ingredients under “Meatballs” in a large bowl and mix by hand. Form into tiny balls and fry in a pan. Set aside for later. - For the soup saute onions, garlic, carrots, and celery until fragrant and soft. Deglaze with white wine, and add equal parts chicken and beef stock. Integrate your orzo pasta and top with a bay leaf and let simmer for a few minutes.  - After that add your meatballs in, remove the bayleaf and top with chopped spinach. Allow to simmer for another few minutes.  - Top with more parmesan cheese, serve and enjoy! #Soups #asmr #ASMRCooking

video_name: 🇵🇭 Arroz Caldo | Soups So Good It Can Cure Any Sickness Ep. 11 INGREDIENTS: Arroz Caldo: - 1kg bone-in chicken thighs - 1 cup glutinous rice (malagkit) - 1 cup regular white rice - 1 onion, chopped - 10-12 garlic cloves, minced - 1 whole ginger, julienned - Chicken oil (optional) - 6-8 cups chicken stock (or until pot is filled) - 2 tbsp fish sauce (or to taste) - Salt and pepper, to taste - 1 tbsp of kasubha Toppings: - Hard-boiled eggs - Fried garlic bits - Spring onions INSTRUCTIONS: - Start by searing your chicken thighs in neutral oil (or in this case we used chicken oil) for about 3-5 minutes on each side. Remove chicken and place on a wire rack. Set aside for later.  - In the same pan or pot add your chopped onions, garlic and ginger and saute using the excess oil until softened and fragrant.  - Add your rice and chicken stock and mix. Add back your chicken thighs and season with fish sauce, kasubha, and pepper. Cover your pot which should be on a gentle simmer for about 25-35 minutes or until the rice is cooked. - Serve with spring onions, eggs, and crispy garlic bits and enjoy! #asmr #ASMRCooking #Soups

video_name: Duck Donburi 🦆🍚 INGREDIENTS: Duck: - Duck breast - Salt and pepper to taste Sauce: - 2 stalk green onion - 6pcs dried shiitake mushrooms - 1 sheet of kombu kelp - 1/2 cup mirib - 1/4 cup sake - 1/2 cup soy sauce - ½ cup sugar - 1 tsp cup of dashi powder Cured Egg Yolk: - egg yolks, whites separated - equal parts mirin and soy sauce Sushi Rice: - Japanese rice - Sushi vinegar to taste Served with: - Ikura (optional) INSTRUCTIONS: - Prior to making the dish, make some cured egg yolks with the ingredients under “Cured Egg Yolk” and allow them to sit in the fridge for 4–6 hours. - Score your duck and season with salt and pepper. Add into a hot pan and sear it to get a nice crust, and baste with oil. - Add to an oven at 200F until internal temp reaches 135F or to your liking - In the meantime, make your l sauce by combining all the ingredients under “sauce”in a saucepan. Bring the mixture to a simmer and reduce until slightly thick before removing from heat and straining the liquid. - Make the sushi rice and add it into a hangiri or a decent-sized bowl, then add some sushi vinegar and mix - Serve everything in a bowl with the sushi rice, add the sauce, and top with ikura and your cured egg yolks. Enjoy! #duck #donburi #ASMR #asmrcooking

video_name: Lamb in Apricot Sauce | Medieval Meals Ep. 12 This dish carries inspiration from the Silk Roads, where spices, fruits, and ideas flowed into Europe. Far from being isolated, medieval tables were shaped by trade routes that stretched across continents. Additionally for any depictions made of barbarians it’s important to note the popular image of wild raiders was just a fantasy. Barbarians in a traditional sense were skilled traders, craftsmen, and farmers — their lives far richer and more complex than the myths suggest. Disclaimer: While the content is inspired by real research from medieval times, the video incorporates elements of medieval faction and fiction for the purposes of entertainment. Researchers: - Igi Gomez Resources: - Adamson, M. W. (2004). Food in medieval times. Greenwood Press. - Hieatt, C. B., Butler, B., & Hosington, S. (1976). Pleyn delit: Medieval cookery for modern cooks. University of Toronto Press. INGREDIENTS:  - 2 lbs boneless lamb, in chunks - 1 lbs of lamb shanks, scored - Salt and pepper to taste - Oil or lard for frying - 1–2 onions, chopped - ⅓ cup of ground almonds - ½ lb dried apricots - Beef broth til pot is filled - 1 tsp ground ginger - 1 tsp ground coriander  INSTRUCTIONS:  - Start by scoring your lamb shanks and cutting your meat into bite sized cubes. Fry them in lard or oil until golden and set aside.  - In the same pot, saute onions until softened, and add ground almonds, apricots and beef stock. Season with ginger, coriander, pepper, and salt, and place in a heat-safe blender. Blend until thick. - Return the meat into the pot, and simmer for 20-30 minutes. Serve and enjoy! #medievalfood #darkfantasy #medieval #lightfantasy

video_name: ARRANCA EL MUNDIAL DE LA GASTRONOMÍA 🏆🍴 19 países, 19 comidas, un solo país ganador ✨ • Vimos que el crack de @Ibai hizo un mundial de desayunos, y no quisimos quedarnos atrás! Acá no hay penales ni VAR: los que deciden son ustedes 👀 • Cada ronda se define con sus votos en las encuestas que vamos a dejar abajo, eligiendo quién pasa a la siguiente fase hasta llegar a la gran final. • De Argentina con su asado 🥩 a Japón con su onigiri 🍙, de México con tacos 🌮 a Francia con boeuf bourguignon 🇫🇷… el fixture está lleno de duelos picantes. • Nosotros nos encargamos de cocinar, pero ustedes tienen la última palabra. • 📲 Voten, comenten, hagan hinchada por su país o por su plato favorito. • Y cuéntenos: ¿Qué receta no puede faltar? ¿Cuál es el cruce que más esperan ver? • Esto recién empieza y ya estamos manija 🔥 • #recetas #mundial #worldcup

video_name: HELADITOS DE BANANA, COCO Y CHOCOLATE: la combinación que nunca falla 🍌🍫 • Una receta simple y fresca, perfecta para tener lista en el freezer. Pero si querés ir a lo seguro, los vasitos descartables siempre están a la mano 😉 • 👩🏼‍🍳 INGREDIENTES: • 4 Bananas maduras 🍌 • 1 cda de Miel 🍯 • 1/2 taza de Bebida 100% vegetal de coco @laserenisimaok 🥥 • Esencia de Vainilla ✨ • Dulce de leche colonial de @laserenisimaok 🥄 • Chocolate semiamargo 🍫 • Fáciles, frescos y con ingredientes que seguro ya tenés en casa. video_name: TAMAGO SANDO Y ATÚN SANDO: un clásico japonés, fácil y rápido 🥪✨ •  Tenía muchas ganas de probar estos sando al estilo japonés para salir un poco de los sándwiches de siempre. Allá son re clásicos, los venden en estaciones y kioscos, pero bueno… como estamos medio lejos, los hice en casa y quedaron buenísimos. 🙌🏼 •  ✨ Tip: para el tamago, separé las claras de las yemas cuando ya estaban cocidas. Hice un puré con las yemas y piqué las claras bien chiquitas antes de mezclar con la mayo y la crema. Queda mucho más parejo y cremoso, se integra mejor con el pan y posta vale la pena tomarse ese ratito. • 👩🏼‍🍳 INGREDIENTES: Tamago Sando (huevo): • 8 huevos 🥚 • Mayonesa Natura 🥄 • Ciboulette 🌿 • Crema 🥛 • Sal 🧂 • Pimienta 🌶️ • Atún Sando: • 2 latas de atún 🐟 • Mayonesa Natura 🥄 • 1 tomate 🍅 • 1 palta 🥑 • 1/2 cebolla morada 🧅 • 30 ml de crema 🥛 • Para los dos: • Pan bien suave 🍞 • Quedan muy buenos así que vale la pena probarlos... ¡Contame cuál te animás a hacer! 😍✨ • #recetas #sandwich #japan

video_name: Maybe you can help me think this through? When I started six years ago, I planned to hire a chef who could bring my ideas to life better than I could. I’d run the floor and manage the service side, which is also my area of strength. The bigger vision was to expand quickly and eventually open a brunch café–bakery concept. But fast forward to now, and things have considerably changed. I don’t see myself necessarily doing a brunch spot anymore and gruelling away on scrambled eggs 7 days a week or leading service (at least not right away). If anything now, I see myself more than ever in the kitchen instead. There are obvious trade-offs. It could slow down my growth with the initial launch, and I might not be as visible as I originally planned. But if I prove myself in the kitchen and do it well, it solidifies my credibility beyond just “playing” with fruits and with flashy edits to, a perhaps, legitimate, skilled chef. So, as I begin to double down more on my future vision, I’ve been increasingly torn about where to focus now, whether to begin with pastry or a restaurant concept, and which one should become the flagship aka driving force that sets the tone for everything to come. Pastry, brunch, cafe, bakery fine dining, pub... what do you see first?

bio:
Te muestro mi día siendo una maestra y creadora de contenido 🇨🇴👩🏻‍🏫
Ig: laprofetatiana
video_name: Respuesta a @Liz🧚 ¡Graciasssssss padre amado por esto! En serio no me lo creo. A mis estudiantes, también gracias por ser tan bellos conmigo, como les dije, Dios me bendice y yo comparto eso que Dios me da con ustedes. ¡Por favor ya no me saquen más canas! 🙈🫶🏼👩🏻‍🏫 Ahora, Los profes no estamos obligados a dar regalos. 🫠 Cuando lo hacemos, es porque nos nace, porque podemos, y porque sentimos que nuestros estudiantes lo valoran. (Aunque muchas veces, algunos no valoran) No todos los docentes tienen esa posibilidad, y eso no los hace menos. Tú profe tiene la obligación de compartir contigo conocimientos, NADA MÁS.  Si alguna vez dijiste 'yo quiero una profe así', pregúntate también: ¿yo qué hago para que mi profe quiera ser especial conmigo? El cariño se gana, se cultiva y se agradece. Valora el esfuerzo, la paciencia, el tiempo… porque incluso los pequeños detalles, a veces, cuestan mucho más de lo que imaginas.  Profes, por favor, no sientan que deben dar detalles. Yo muchas veces he desistido de hacerlo porque considero que mis estudiantes no lo valoran. (Tengo Storytime y que tales). 🤭😑 Mi intención al compartir estos acontecimientos es agradecer a las personas, a mis seguidores a Dios por todas las bendiciones. Espero puedan comprenderlo.  #profe #maestra #profetatiana #docente

video_name: SUSHI BAKE i was lying bout the 6 7 billion views😄 6 7 is trending right now lmaoo SALMON MIXTURE 2 salmon filets ½ imitation crab 5 oz cream cheese, soften preferred 1/3 cup Japanese mayo 2 TBSP sirarcha 3-4 sheets of seaweed RICE 3 cups cooked white rice 1 tsp mirin 1 tsp rice vinegar Salt to taste TO SERVE: seaweed avocado cucumbers jalpenos 1. Season your salmon filets with: salt, black pepper, paprika and olive oil. Cook using your preferred method… airfryer, stovetop or oven. I air fried mine at 400F for 12 minutes. 2. Shred your imitation crab and then cut smaller so the strips aren’t too long. 3. By now, your salmon should be done cooking. Add your cooked salmon you’re your shredded imitation crab.  Break the salmon apart. If there is skin on you salmon, then discard. 4. Add 5 oz soften cream cheese, 1/3 cup cream cheese and 2 TBSP sirarcha. Combine this well, set this aside. 5. In a baking dish (mine is 9x13), add 3 cups of cooked white rice. Season rice with: 1 tsp mirin, 1 tsp rice vinegar and salt to taste. Combine this well then flatten the rice into the baking dish. 6. Next, top your rice with shredded seaweed or furikake. 7. Add an even layer of salmon mixture on top your rice + seaweed. Bake at 380F for 10 minutes, then broil for 3-5 minutes. 8. Drizzle some siracha and spicy mayo on top of your sushi bake. Garnish with chopped scallion and black sesame seeds. 9. Serve with seaweed and other toppings like jalapenos, cucumbers and/ or avocados.

video_name: DUA CHUA - PICKLED MUSTARD GREENS INGREDIENTS 2 bundles of mustard greens (large Gai chow) 4 cups water 2 cups sugar 2 cups vinegar 2 tsp salt INSTRUCTIONS Cut mustard greens into 1 - 1.5 in pieces. Wash throughly and place into a large enough air tight container (note: musard greens are very dirty so make sure you wash it several times) 2. In a mixing bowl, combine: water, sugar, vinegar and salt. Mix until sugar is dissolved and then pour this mixture over your mustard greens. Let this sit at room temp for 2 days then move into the fridge for at least 1 week before enjoying.

video_name: STOVE TOP BO KHO Recipe is from my bestie @Tracey Le | JustlikeMoms    BEEF MARINADE 2-3 lb chuck roast 3 TBSP minced garlic 1 TBSP chicken bouillon ½ TBSP salt 1 TBSP fish sauce 3 TBSP hoisin sauce 1 oz bo kho/ beef stew seasoning* *1 bag of bo kho seasoning is 2 oz so you need 1 oz. You will use the other half later   BEEF STEW 3 TBSP minced garlic 1  oz bo kho seasoning 1/3 cup @heinz tomato ketchup 2 TBSP hoisin sauce 8 stalks of lemongrass 2 cans chicken stock (14.5 oz each can) 1 can coco rico/ coconut soda (12 oz each can) 3 cups hot water 1 yellow or white onion, cut into large chunks   ADDITIONAL INGREDIENTS 5 carrots, skinned and cut 1 inch Oil, for cooking Cornstarch slurry (3 TBSP cornstarch + 3 TBSP water)   FOR SERVING: Noodles (I used rice noodles/ pho noodles0 French baguette/ crusty bread/ French roll Rice Chopped scallion Chopped cilantro Thinly sliced onions   INSTRUCTIONS 1.        Cut chuck roast into large pieces.   2.        Make your marinade by combining all of the ingredients listed under BEEF MARINADE. Marinate your beef for at least 2 hours.   3.        Prepare your lemongrass: cut off the leafy ends of your lemongrass and discard the leafy end. With the remainder of ur lemongrass, peel the first couple outer layer of your lemongrass and cut a piece piece of the root end off. Then using a mallet or spine of your knife, gently bruise your lemongrass. Cut lemongrass into 3-4 in wide pieces. Set this aside.   4.        In a pot, heat up some oil and saute 3 TBSP garlic until fragrant.   5.        Next add the rest of your bo kho season (1 oz), 1/3 cup Heinz ketchup and 2 TBSP hoisin sauce. Combine well.   6.        Next, add your prepared lemongrass and cook for a couple of minutes.   7.        Add marinated beef and cook for ~5 minutes.   8.        Then add 2 cans of chicken broth, 1 can coco rico and 3 cups hot water, and 1 yellow or white onion. Bring this to a boil and then reduce heat, cover and simmer for at least 1.5 hours. I let mine simmer for 2.5 hours. During the simmering process, you will get foam that floats to the top, skim the foam out.   9.        After you are done simmering, add carrots and cook for another 10 minutes or until your carrots are fork tender.   10.  Thicken your beef stew by cranking heat to high and adding a slurry (3 TBSP cornstarch + 3 TBSP water). Leave this to cook for 3-5 minutes.. ur stew will slightly thicken.   11.  Now assemble a bowl.  I like to eat my beef stew with pho noodles. If u prefer to eat with bread, you can do that as well. Assemble a bowl with: pho noodles, stew, chopped scallion, chopped cilantro, thinly sliced onions, lime juice and/or chili oil.

video_name: CANH CHUA – SOUR SOUP   Kimchi Jiggae translates to kimchi soup. Canh chua translates to “sour soup”. Canh = soup. Chua = sour.   1 lb pork riblets 8-9 cups water ½ large yellow onion ~5 cups pickled mustard greens 3 TBSP mushroom seasoning 1 tsp tamarind powder 2 tsp salt 1.5 TBSP rock sugar 2 roma tomatoes Hand full chopped scallion   1.        Par boil riblets for 5 minutes and then rinse and drain under cold water. 2.        In a pot, add your parboiled pork riblets, ½ large onion, and 8-9 cups of water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, cover and reduce heat to simmer. Simmer for 25 minutes. At the 15-minute mark, re fill water if needed (because some water will evaporate) 3.        After 25 minutes of simmering, remove your onion. Add pickled mustard greens and season with: 3 TBSP mushroom seasoning, 1 tsp tamarind powder, 2 tsp salt, and 2 TBSP rock sugar. Bring this back to a boil 4.        Add tomatoes wedges and chopped scallion. Immediately turn off heat.

bio: I'm journalist & motorcycle reviewer @otomotif_tv @otomotifweekly_ @gridoto.com
video_name: CUSTOMAXi 2025 seri pertama pecah banget! Berlangsung di Queen City Mall, Semarang, Jawa Tengah akhir pekan lalu (20-21 September 2025), totalnya ada 80 motor ikut adu keren konsep modifikasi.  Ada di video kali ini, kita lihat beberapa modifikasi yang keren-keren! Dari 2 kelas utama yaitu STREET MAXi dan SUPER MAXi. untuk masing-masing tipe motor mulai dari XMAX, NMAX, AEROX sampai LEXi. Bukan hanya kontes modifikasi, ada juga beberapa keseruan lainnya, seperti tatto temporary, photobooth AI, sampai live painting. Minggu ini, CUSTOMAXi 2025 giliran menyambangi Makassar, Sulawesi Selatan sebagai kota kedua. Minggu, 28 September 2025 bertempat di Mari Arcade, Mall Ratu Indah. Jangan sampai enggak dateng ya! #customaxi #customaxi2025 #yamahalexi #xmax #aerox #aeroxmodifikasi #aerox155 #nmax #nmaxmodifikasi

bio: I'm journalist & motorcycle reviewer @otomotif_tv @otomotifweekly_ @gridoto.com
video_name: Gak tau motor siapa hehe.. Tag ya kalau ada yang tahu ownernya. Kedua Honda NSR250R MC28 ini jadi salah satu magnet yang bikin langkah pengunjung berhenti di IMOS 2025.  Honda NSR250 MC28 ini masuk kategori racing replica dan dirilis pertama kali pada Oktober 1993. Pakai mesin 2-tak V-twin 249cc powernya 40 hp, transmisi 6 percepatan, dan sudah pakai fitur RC Valve. Salah satu fitur paling keren di zamannya adalah PGM Memory Card berfungsi sebagai microchip dengan engine mapping berbeda. Powernya bisa naik dari 40 hp ke 65 hp. Gokils.  Btw, yang merah sudah upgrade kaki-kaki pakai USD dan upgrade rem. Cakep ya! #nsr #nsr250 #nsr250r #nsr150 #hondansr

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: Since so many thought I blocked the vents with the @ragofabrication dash mount I figured may as well block the controls for them too hahahaha • I got this @midlandradio two way radio and figured this would give it a good place to mount as well as other stuff • The instructions said to pull apart the console but I used Rivnuts instead and it worked perfect. I didn’t have to pull anything apart • I don’t know about you but I loose Allen keys the week I get them, I’ve had this @gearwrenchtools T-handle set for years now and haven’t lost any of them. I feel like the labeled rack being on this tool chest keeps me inline • These @ragofabrication are available @4Runner Lifestyle

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: Added this @Kimpex USA front and back windshield to the Maverick • This was a massive upgrade that took no time to install. The wind that goes through the cab is insane, it pulls on the helmets and there is no way to talk to each other • It’s made of 1/4” polycarbonate which is 250x stronger than glass and 25x stronger than acrylic. The reason I wanted this over glass is because I pull it on my flat deck and don’t want to crack the glass • I’ve sure been using this 1/4” @gearwrenchtools torque wrench a lot lately. It definitely fills the void that the 1/2” and 3/8” can’t get down to. Comes with a nice case as well  . . . #tools #kimpex #gearwrench #canam #maverickx3turborr

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: On our journey @Overland Expo we met @Slouch Couch  • This really got my interest because room can be tight when packing for an adventure but having a loveseat on hand would be so cool • So here’s the info It has a built in USB C rechargeable inflator/deflator. It inflates in 90 seconds. The material is 500D nylon condura so it can take a beating • The storage bag is way bigger than the couch so it’s super easy to get back in • They have it on their website right now $70 off making it $280 • It’s definitely become the favorite place to sit when we are out . . . #tools #camping #couch #furniture #slouchcouch

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: If you have installed a lot of rivets by hand you can definitely appreciate this tool • This Hilti Rivet tool runs on their Nuron battery platform. All you have to do is press the trigger and it does the rest. It keeps things consistent. • It has a spot for the different size nose pieces and has a container to catch the mandrel @Hilti North America  . . . #tools #construction #hiltipartner #hilti #hiltitools

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: Gotta make sure you do the right prep work!! • I’m going to coat this floor and ramp but before that I need to sand down this floor and vacuum it many times to make sure the product will adhere properly • I decided to go with this 5” Bosch sander. No cord and I ran it with the bag • I went over this floor twice sanding it for over 30 min straight. I ran the 4ah core battery and by the end it was still showing 2 out of 5 bars • I had to empty the bag 3 times as well. It worked really good • Next I’ll put a few coats down on the floor. They use 3/4 plywood for the floor in the @Southland Trailer Corp.  @Bosch Power Tools  . . . #tools #construction #boschpartner #boschtools #construction

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: I never thought I’d be moving around my @Southland Trailers cargo trailer with a Makita drill • With the @Trailer Valet it’s possible! • I saw this like 5 years ago at a trade show and figured it would be handy! Wait till you see what I do with it next. @Makita Tools USA @Makita Canada Inc.  . . . #tools #construction #trailervalet #makita #makitatools

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: Where you live are you using clipped head or full round head nails in your nailer? • Here we use clipped, it’s actually pretty hard to find a box of full round in stores here. Sorta a special order thing • This is the @FLEXPOWERTOOLSNA framing nailer. I pulled it straight outta the box and took it right to this saturated pressure treated 6x6. • I got 3-1/4” nails in it and set it to full depth. I’ve used pretty much every battery powered framing nailer on the market and I’m sure you will agree that the faster you go the chance or a proud nail is way higher • I was surprised to see that it was the opposite with this, it was straight up burning the nails even further with speed. I do think I could have even pushed it faster • This will be the nailer that goes in my tool trailer build so you’ll see more of it soon . . . #tools #construction #framing #carpentry #flexpartner

bio: Murray Kruger
video_name: Makita has just announced New 18v nailers! • Here is the angled 16g It can take 1-1/4 to 2-1/2 • So let’s toss in a compact battery and some 2-1/2 nails and see how it does • First some spruce with ease, I found some maple cutoffs and left in the 2-1/2. Now it is a full depth and as you can see it had no problem and even at that speed it kept them sinking at a consistent depth • Now bump fire isn’t normally something you use on a nailer like this but it does show the power of it, especially with that small battery • It has a light, a couple extra nose adapters and belt clip. Oh and it’s made in Japan @Makita Tools USA  . . . #tools #construction #makita #makitatools #makitapartner

video_name: Pesawat kecil seperti Cessna atau Piper menggunakan bahan bakar khusus yang disebut AVGAS 100LL (Aviation Gasoline). Angka ‘100’ menunjukkan angka oktan yang sangat tinggi, artinya bahan bakar ini mampu menahan panas dan tekanan tinggi tanpa menyebabkan knocking (ledakan dini di mesin). Kenapa harus begitu? Mesin pesawat saat take-off dan climb bekerja pada putaran tinggi dan beban maksimum. Kalau diisi dengan bensin mobil biasa seperti Pertalite (oktan 90), mesin bisa mengalami knocking parah, tenaga turun, getaran berlebih, suhu cepat naik, hingga berisiko merusak mesin. Analoginya seperti motor sport 250cc yang dipaksa minum bensin oktan rendah. Memang bisa jalan, tapi performa berkurang, mesin cepat panas, dan umur komponen lebih pendek. Bedanya, kalau motor mogok bisa berhenti di pinggir jalan, sedangkan pesawat harus tetap aman di udara. Karena itu, pemilihan bahan bakar bukan sekadar pilihan, tapi soal keselamatan penerbangan.

video_name: Pesawat latih Piper Warrior menggunakan mesin andalan Pabrikan Lycoming O-320-D3G, mesin piston 4 silinder berpendingin udara. Walaupun kapasitasnya ‘hanya’ sekitar 160 tenaga kuda, mesin ini terkenal bandel, sederhana, dan mudah dirawat, cocok untuk pesawat latih yang dipakai sehari-hari. Mesin ini bisa dibilang ‘partner belajar’ yang sabar. Tahan dipakai untuk take-off pendek, touch-and-go berulang kali, hingga latihan stall dan manuver dasar. Justru karena ketangguhannya, banyak sekolah pilot di seluruh dunia menjadikan Piper Warrior sebagai kuda kerja mereka. Kalau mau dianalogikan, Lycoming O-320 itu seperti mesin motor touring 4-tak yang tahan banting. Bukan yang paling kencang, tapi bisa diajak jalan jauh, tangguh di berbagai kondisi, dan jarang rewel kalau dirawat benar. Bedanya, motor touring kalau mogok tinggal minggir, sedangkan Piper Warrior harus tetap terbang dengan aman. Itulah kenapa mesin ini dirancang simpel, teruji, dan bisa diandalkan. Btw @ppicurug.official @penerbangppic punya 2 tipe pesawat latih Single Engine, yakni Piper Warrior III dan Piper Archer III Garmin 1000, nice banget kan 👌🏻

video_name: Replying to @Joyce Chamberlain Ta Day 14: final day🎉🎉 Meet my very first Mes Amis Toys elephant 🐘🩶 what should we name it??? Thank you so so so much for sticking around for two full weeks while I created this gentle giant. I hope you all loved this series as much as I enjoyed making it!! Words cannot express how thankful I am to have such an encouraging, loving, engaged audience to share my craziness with🩷  • Outfit from @AKIRA  • #crochet #fyp #crochetersoftiktok #series #mesamistoys

bio:
"Maze a-mee" 🧸
Home of the crochet statues
Snapchat @mes.amistoys
video_name: Day 9: did we finally figure it out???? I was able to move the whole body and lift the front but holding the secured “neck bone” 2x4 so I trust that it’s stable enough and will hold up the head.  I originally thought that I was going to secure the 2x4s starting at the back of the body so that the weight was equally distributed. I ended up using a hanger bracket instead, because it’ll do the job and I’m afraid of adding that much height into the middle of the body. The stuffing will settle a little bit overtime and I don’t want it to create this hump in the center. I didn’t add the underbelly yet, and am moving onto the head tomorrow because that’s a whole other challenge I need to face while I have the courage to do so. The belly is quite simple so I’ll do this in a few days and sew it onto the body later.  #crochet #fyp #art #mesamistoys #series #crochetersoftiktok

video_name: Replying to @qween nay Day 8: I love the days when I can just stitch around and not pay much attention to what I’m doing. No stitch marker, just vibes✨ I promise I’m going to figure out this wood situation tomorrow, it’s been haunting me but I can’t do anymore on the body without attaching it #crochet #fyp #art #mesamistoys #series #crochetersoftiktok #amigurumi

Being her mom is the greatest thing I’ll ever do. I prayed for it. I also haven’t left the house alone in 4 months. Motherhood is not all sunshine and rainbows. Sometimes it’s a scary, lonely, confusing, transformative, existential rollercoaster.  I’m gonna call this one “The Death of Her Old Self”  ✍️

video_name: The buttercream rose 🌹  This is my main statement flower and you'll find it in almost every bouquet I make. Buttercream roses aren't the easiest to pipe (they take patience and practice!) but if you're learning how to make cupcake flowers, this is the one to master. The results are always stunning and really elevate your bouquet. Top tip - always keep your piping bag tight, don’t be scared to put the cupcake down, re-tighten your bag and carry on 🙂. Nozzle details and what it looks like are in the video.  #buttercreamroses #cupcakebouquet #buttercreamflowers #cakedecorating #cupcakearmy

Every clip is a reminder that big dogs are not monsters, they are family, companions, and sometimes the biggest goofballs you will ever meet. video_name: If u have an impulse to get a cat…. Take this as a sign because I met george at an animal welfare league adoption center when I was 19 yrs old and visited a mall. Was not planning on getting a cat at all but saw 3 month old george and got the impression he was perfect and amazing. I left without him but kept thinking about him, walking around the mall thinking maybe I should go back. I decided to go back and asked for a sign if I should really impulsively adopt a kitten. When I went back someone else was saying goodbye to him, deciding not to adopt him. I took that as my sign and paid $50 for a fully neutered, vaxxed and microchipped kitren, shocked that they let me take him home as a 19 yr old college student. It shows you how many cats need homes that i was deemed good enough. I Never expected him to become an actual keyboard cat but here we are 10 yrs later. I’m about to turn 30 and he’a been my best buddy for over a decade now. #adoptdontshop #animalwelfareleague

video_name: Day 3 and I’m already a city boy. I rode the subway, conquered the metra, and even made a new best friend who’s about three times my size. We wrestled, we ran, and then I crashed. I was out cold on the train, snoring while strangers laughed. My secret weapon? The gym bag. Forget cars, forget kennels — carry me like your lunch and I’ll curl up happy. I’ll even climb in when we’re not going anywhere, just to snooze. City adventures, big friends, bag naps. Foster life looks good on me. Available @Chicago Canine Rescue  #adoptdontshop #fosterdog #pittiemix

video_name: I don’t work for free. If you want tricks out of me, you better sweet talk first. It’s day two in my foster home and I’m already getting comfy. I’ve picked out my favorite snooze spots, and I take my gardening duties outside very seriously. Mealtime? That’s my toughest test. I have to sit there and resist, sometimes I can’t even look at my bowl until I get the okay. By the end of the night, I’m out cold — stuffy in my mouth, tucked into my crate, dreaming of tomorrow. Available @Chicago Canine Rescue  #adoptdontshop #fosterdog #pittiemix

video_name: It’s day six, and I’m starting to get the hang of this. I spend most of the day recharging, I’ve been feeling a little down. But I still show my puppy burst of energy. I finally had my first solid poop (yes, that’s worth celebrating). We picked up new meds and I was surprised with a new toy. I loved it so much I carried it around the block and even into my kennel. We ended the day the best way possible: pretzel snuggles on the couch, then straight to bed. Shelter life feels far away now. Available @Chicago Canine Rescue

video_name: My foster dad promised me I’ll never end up in the shelter again. It’s Day 5 in my foster home and things are looking up. My tummy’s finally settling, my walks are getting easier, and I’m starting to feel more comfortable in the neighborhood. I even made a new friend today—gave her a good ear sniff for approval. When I’m not on neighborhood watch duty, you’ll find me stretched out, dreaming away, and enjoying this new chapter. Available @Chicago Canine Rescue

video_name: Okay I messed up. It’s day 4 and I pooped my pants. I got a bath. My kennel got scrubbed. I gave my best “sorry and thank you” face. My tummy’s been upset, but foster dad’s got me on meds and chicken-and-rice to help me feel better. While I napped, he went to take pictures of other shelter dogs. I didn’t know where he went… but I was so happy when he came back. By bedtime I claimed the couch instead of going upstairs. Foster life is exhausting, but I think I’m getting the hang of it. video_name: Today was a big day. My foster grandparents came to visit and spoiled me with toys, treats, and way too much love. (Not that I’m complaining.) It was time for the Super Adoption event. I got to cheer on my foster dad while he took pictures of all the adoptable dogs. So many pups found their forever homes yesterday. But some are still waiting. They’re just as deserving, just as ready, and just as hopeful as me. I’ve already had lots of adoption interest, and I’ve even got an appointment lined up. But if you’re looking to adopt, don’t forget about my friends still at the shelter. They’re waiting for their fan club too.

bio:
La vie d’un photographe animalier 🇫🇷 

Précommander mon livre ORANGE & WILD
video_name: Aviez vous entendu parlé de cet animal ? Je n’ai pu l’observer que 3 petites minutes. Puis il s’est enfoncé dans la forêt sans jamais revenir.  C’est l’ours le plus rare du monde. Retranché sur une île en Colombie Britannique et considéré comme une divinité par les populations autochtones. Heureux de vous partager ma rencontre avec l’ours Esprit dans l’Ouest canadien.  #nature #animaux #ours #canada🇨🇦 #photographe

bio:
La vie d’un photographe animalier 🇫🇷 

Précommander mon livre ORANGE & WILD
video_name: C’est le seul endroit au monde où il est possible de les observer à pied !J’ai choisi de photographier l’ours blanc dans la Bais d’Hudson au Canada pour avoir mon objectif au même niveau que leur regard (mes photos à la fin). Pour cela, il faut avoir des guides d’une grande expérience, capables d’anticiper le comportement de l’ours polaire 🤠 Les ours blancs sont des animaux redoutables, et chaque année, on recense des accidents. Ils seraient un peu plus de 20.000 sur la planète. Leurs menaces : la chasse, le braconnage, la pollution et le réchauffement climatique 🎥 #ours #canada #animaux #photographe #safari @Churchill Wild

bio:
La vie d’un photographe animalier 🇫🇷 

Précommander mon livre ORANGE & WILD
video_name: Je suis parti à l’autre bout de la planète, en Colombie Britannique au Canada pour les photographier ! Mes photos de ces P’tites peluches à la fin 🥰 Autrefois braconnées et chassées pour leur fourrure, les loutres de mer ont bien failli disparaître. Aujourd’hui, elle est protégée et Tofino reste le meilleur endroit du monde pour les photographier.  #animaux #loutre #canada #photographe #safari

bio:
La vie d’un photographe animalier 🇫🇷 

Précommander mon livre ORANGE & WILD
video_name: J’ai déjà vu des centaines de lions mais il m’aura fallu plus de 20 ans de safaris pour filmer cette scène. Pourquoi un allaitement est-il si rare à observer ? D’abord, parce que ce moment ne dure que 7 mois dans la vie d’un lionceau. Enfin, parce que la lionne doit se sentir en pleine confiance et sans stress pour laisser les petits allaiter. Cela nécessite une approche délicate et respectueuse. Et de la patience, beaucoup de patience. Un moment inoubliable: mes vidéos à la fin.  #safari #animaux #nature #lion #photographe

bio:
La vie d’un photographe animalier 🇫🇷 

Précommander mon livre ORANGE & WILD
video_name: Quel moment ! Après plusieurs jours à les chercher, les indices manquent cruellement. Seules quelques traces dans la neige, parfois même un chant au loin. Mais pas la moindre silhouette de cet animal si emblématique. Et puis, une heure avant mon départ, ils m’ont fait grâce de leur présence…  Photographier les loups du Grand Nord Canadien a été une expérience inoubliable. Merci à @Churchill Wild pour ce moment hors du temps et dont je me souviendrai toute ma vie. Et si je retournais au Nabil Polar Bear Lodge ? #animaux #loup #nature #canada #safari

video_name: O primeiro melhor amigo do Will foi seu irmão Iron. Buscamos os dois juntos em Minas Gerais na cidade de um colega de trabalho do Diego, pois a mãezinha deles havia dado cria a 8 filhotinhos.  Will e Iron se viam sempre que dava. Um posava na casa do outro já que Iron foi adotado por um casal da nossa cidade.  Até que perdemos esse costume deles se encontrarem.  Depois desse afastamento, Will ficou por mais de 3 anos sem ter um melhor amigo cachorro para brincar. Até que a Clarinha chegou.  Will e Claramela tem a mesma conexão de Will e Iron. E até na cor caramelo os dois se parecem.  Atualmente Iron está bem. Enorme. Ele é a cara do pai deles que é um Pit Monster.  Mesmo tendo adotado a Clara já adulta, na minha visão, ela e o Will sempre serão duas crianças. Meus bebês ❤️ #cachorros #cachorro #pitbull #filhote #filhotes

bio: Actriță 🎭 | Umor 🌟 | Inimă română ❤️
video_name: Dragostea pentru necuvântătoare cred că vine din naștere. Grija față de ele… se învață și nu este întotdeauna ușor să le îngrijești cum se cuvine și cu respect. Mai ales cand ai multe. 😊 Am acceptat cu bucurie invitația (celor de la) @Fressnapf Romania de a le vizita unul din magazinele din Bucuresti și este un loc unde ma voi reintoarce constant. Reacțiile mele din clip sunt cât se poate de autentice: am găsit o gamă variată de produse la prețuri incredibile!!! Am apreciat enorm și ajutorul medicului lor veterinar, iar prezența angajaților experimentați este foarte reconfortantă, deoarece poți discuta cu experți despre nevoile fiecărui animăluț. Când le calcati pragul, trebuie neapărat să le si descoperiți produsele proprii: Multifit, Premiere și Select Gold! Despre răsfățații mei de acasa ce să vă spun? Unii entuziasmati si agitati, altii au refuzat categoric să apară în video, altii au acceptat cu greu si timid doar o fotografie, iar ultimul nazdravan din video?... nici măcar atât 😊. Află mai multe pe www.fresnapf.ro #fresnapf #ad @fresnapf.romania

video_name: There is a way you go about things. Never interacting with specific  creators , copying their personality , aesthetic, lyrics , buying the same exact props they use in their videos , never showing them love on their videos , and then going and putting their name in a song for clout is NOT the way to do it.  Is there space for everyone YES, should you have your own style and personality YES. Should you copy other people in the same space as you, NO!  Am I the only one doing what I’m doing NO , but PLEASE don’t down right copy. People see what works for me and my audience so they watch , copy and then mention my name in their song because they KNOW the fans will react a certain way . That’s not love that is mockery and it’s not okay. Because IF the love was genuine they would be interacting with me not watching and copying . I have 4 different songs / free styles where I say “I sing I rap I hoop , I teach. “ I have MULTIPLE different songs where I say I teach babies how to speak / talk .” I have SEVERAL videos of me hooping dating back past 2023 . I’ve BEEN doing this. So to have my name mentioned in a video of a person using extremely similar lyrics and hooping in the video is disturbing and it’s basically taunting me.  I’m not the only person this creator has copied they also copied someone else all the way down to the same outfit and headwear . So I’m not the only one this is happening to in this situation . Share the space YES , Be inspired YES, Copy NO.  And NO I’m not hating on anyone , I’m speaking facts . The viewers don’t see it from the lense I see it in and that’s fine .  I’m going to leave you with this: they shouted out 5 major black female kid yt creators in their song , but follow NONE of the people they shouted out . They follow a ton of other kid yt creators but didn’t shout them out in the song .  So was it showing love or was it calculated to get a reaction out of our fans to make it appear that they support . And that’s a rhetorical question . #mshouston #freestyle

video_name: American traveler is left stunned after trying Robotic legs in China 🇨🇳 This occurred in Zhangjiajie National Park and is the follow up to a previous video of the robotic legs. Here you can see me getting set up with the robotic suite, and explaination on how it is used, running, and even the price  These robotic legs are rented out to people in the national park to help with hiking. For rent it is $22 but to buy them for personal use is $950. These robotic legs are so crazy, you can control how much power and sometimes it doesn’t even feel like you are walking #fyp #tellme #traveltiktok #china #chongqing

video_name: An American traveler is left speechless after experiencing a futuristic library in China 🇨🇳  This video is from Chengdu China, the city of Panda bears. Chengdu is a tier 1 city meaning it is of the highest standards in China. This library is located on the 3rd floor of a shopping mall and you would have no idea it is there just from seeing the entrance.  I found the Fangsuo bookstore by accident when I went to have lunch in China. But when I walked inside I could not believe my eyes. Also it is completely free to enter, and you are not obligated to buy a book or even a coffee. Which I think is a major contrast to the USA which would definitely charge an entrance fee. #fyp #tellme #traveltiktok #china #chengdu

video_name: A 26 year old American traveler is left speechless after seeing China for the 1st time 🇨🇳 This occurred in Chengdu China, a city famous for its technology, architecture, and most importantly Pandas. When I 1st arrived in this mega city I could not believe it. It is so different than what we have been taught our entire lives in the USA  We have never been taught a good image of China or what the reality is here. From my experience the past few days I cannot believe how safe it feels, how clean it is, the scale of the cities, and how modern everything is #fyp #tellme #traveltiktok #china #chengdu

video_name: An American traveler is in disbelief after being along in a Chinese national park 🇨🇳  This video is from Zhangjiajie national park one of the most beautiful places in the entire country. Not only is the traveler in disbelief by the trail on the side of the mountain but also how few people are actually there  This is a common sight in China, even though the country has over 1 billion people, many tourist attractions feel a bit empty. In my opinion this is because of how large the country is and how many place there are to see. Of course the time of the year also plays a huge role #fyp #tellme #traveltiktok #china #zhangjiajie

Meski bisa membuat penderitanya khawatir, sebenarnya kondisi ini termasuk jinak dan tidak berbahaya. Cairan di dalamnya berasal dari cairan sinovial, yaitu pelumas alami sendi yang merembes keluar dan terjebak dalam kantung kecil. Bentuknya bisa membesar atau mengecil, bahkan kadang hilang dengan sendirinya tanpa perlu tindakan medis. Namun, pada beberapa orang, kista ganglion dapat menimbulkan rasa nyeri atau menekan saraf di sekitarnya sehingga mengganggu pergerakan. Jika sudah begitu, salah satu solusi medis yang dilakukan adalah operasi kecil untuk mengangkatnya. Proses ini biasanya dilakukan oleh dokter bedah tangan dengan teknik yang cukup sederhana. Tindakan operasi dimulai dengan membuat sayatan kecil di atas area kista. Setelah itu, dokter mencari bagian tangkai atau “stalk” yang menghubungkan kista dengan sendi atau tendon. Bagian stalk inilah yang sering membuat kista bisa tumbuh kembali jika tidak diangkat sepenuhnya. Karena itu, dokter akan dengan hati-hati memotong stalk tersebut sebelum mengangkat kantung kista yang berisi cairan. Setelah kista dikeluarkan, area operasi ditutup kembali dengan jahitan halus. Proses pemulihan biasanya berlangsung cepat, walaupun pasien disarankan untuk mengistirahatkan sendi yang terkena agar tidak menimbulkan tekanan berlebih. Dalam beberapa kasus, kista bisa muncul lagi, tetapi kemungkinan ini jauh lebih kecil setelah operasi dibanding hanya ditusuk atau dikompres. Kisah medis mengenai kista ganglion memperlihatkan bahwa meski terlihat menakutkan, sebenarnya kondisi ini cukup umum dan dapat ditangani dengan prosedur yang relatif aman. Dengan teknik operasi yang tepat, penderita bisa kembali beraktivitas normal tanpa terganggu benjolan di sekitar sendi. #faktaunik #kesehatan #fakesituation⚠️  #fakesituation  #fakebodyy⚠️

bio: La inteligencia puede dividir, la sabiduría siempre unifica
video_name: El veneno de querer infinitas opciones. Hoy nadie se compromete. Queremos todas las puertas abiertas, todos los cuerpos disponibles, todas las promesas sin responsabilidad. Pero esa falsa libertad nos está pudriendo por dentro. La abundancia de opciones en el amor no nos da felicidad: nos deja vacíos, incapaces de elegir, incapaces de sostener. Cuanto más creemos ganar, más perdemos. La verdad es brutal: amar es cerrar caminos. La plenitud no está en tener miles de posibilidades, sino en decidir y morir a todas las demás. Quien huye de esa renuncia, nunca conoce el verdadero amor. #paradojadelaeleccion #amor #conciencia #mandalahealing #gerukaland  --- ¿Quieres que lo lleve a un tono aún más desgarrador y poético, casi como un manifiesto que desnude la herida colectiva del amor líquido actual?

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: ¿Qué es un despertar emocional? Es ese momento en el que, de pronto, empiezas a darte cuenta de cosas que antes ni te planteabas. Sientes diferente. Piensas diferente. Ya no puedes hacer como que no pasa nada con lo que llevas dentro. De repente entiendes que no todo era culpa de los demás. Que muchas de tus reacciones venían de heridas antiguas. Que llevas emociones guardadas desde hace años. Que estar bien no es solo “no llorar” o “tirar pa’lante”. Un despertar emocional no es ir gritando por ahí “¡estoy sanando!”. Es más bien algo silencioso, profundo… A veces incómodo, sí. Pero también muy liberador. Es ese momento en el que empiezas a mirarte con más verdad… y también con más cariño.

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: ¡Hola, mis exploradores del alma! 🌟 En este vídeo os voy a contar el origen del rechazo y del abandono —dos heridas emocionales que muchos llevamos dentro sin darnos cuenta, pero que influyen muchísimo en cómo nos relacionamos, en lo que sentimos y hasta en cómo nos vemos a nosotros mismos. Así que si alguna vez has sentido que no eras suficiente, que te dejaban de lado, o que el miedo a perder a alguien te paraliza… quédate, porque esto te va a resonar. Vamos a explorar juntos desde dónde nace todo esto.

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: La ansiedad siempre llega primero. Se cuela en la mente disfrazada de urgencia, hablándote en susurros que se sienten como gritos: ¿Y si no es suficiente? ¿Y si te equivocas? ¿Y si todo se cae? Habla con miedo, con prisa, con necesidad de controlar. Es ruidosa. Insistente. Agotadora. Quiere respuestas inmediatas, garantías, certezas imposibles. Pero si te das un respiro… si dejas de correr detrás de cada pensamiento… algo más profundo se hace presente. La intuición. Ella no compite por tu atención. No grita. No exige. Solo espera. Y cuando la ansiedad termina de hablar, la intuición responde, suave pero firme: Esto ya lo sabes. Confía en ti. El camino no se ve claro, pero lo estás pisando. Y en ese instante… hay calma. Porque entendés que la ansiedad viene del miedo, pero la intuición nace de la verdad.

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: ¡Hola, mis exploradores del alma! 🌿 En este vídeo os comparto las 3 verdades que nunca voy a olvidar y que cambiaron por completo mi forma de ver el dolor. Si estás cansado de sufrir, de darle vueltas a todo y sentir que nada cambia… quédate, porque estas tres verdades me ayudaron a soltar, a entender y a empezar a vivir con más calma. No son mágicas, pero sí muy reales. Y cuando las integras… todo empieza a tener otro sentido.

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: En este vídeo te voy a contar el secreto para empezar a vencer el miedo y la ansiedad. No es magia, ni fórmulas raras… es algo simple, pero que nadie nos enseña. Y cuando lo entiendes, todo empieza a cambiar

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: Os voy a decir algo que entendí después de una ruptura…” Una ruptura no duele tanto por quien se va. Duele por lo que esa persona tocó dentro de ti. Si te hizo daño, lo que realmente arde no es solo lo que pasó… es la herida que ya llevabas desde antes: el miedo al abandono, el sentir que no eras suficiente, la soledad que ya estaba ahí. Esa persona solo lo activó. No lo creó. Por eso, cuando alguien se va y te rompe, no estás perdiendo el amor de tu vida. Estás viendo la parte de ti que aún necesita tu propio amor. Y ahí empieza la verdadera sanación: cuando dejas de mirar fuera, y empiezas a abrazar lo que dentro pide ser visto.

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: A veces reaccionamos sin pensar: gritamos, cortamos una conversación, mandamos ese mensaje impulsivo, nos encerramos o huimos de una situación. Y uno piensa “bueno, me salió así, no lo pude evitar”. Pero si uno se detiene un segundo a mirar más de cerca… casi siempre hay miedo ahí, escondido. Miedo a que nos lastimen. Miedo a no ser suficientes. Miedo al rechazo, al abandono, a perder el control. Entonces, en vez de decir “tengo miedo”, el cuerpo y la mente reaccionan con lo que tienen a mano: enojo, distancia, ansiedad, llanto, impulsos. Y ojo, no está mal sentir. Solo que cuando entendés que ese impulso no era solo enojo o tristeza, sino un miedo que está pidiendo ser escuchado… todo empieza a tener un poco más de sentido. Y ya no reaccionás igual.

bio: 🎁 Taller gratuito: “3 verdades sobre la ansiedad que nadie te cuenta👇
video_name: A veces decimos “todo va a estar bien” como si fuera un mantra sagrado. Pero la verdad es que muchas veces no lo decimos desde la fe real, sino desde el miedo. Como si fuera una frase mágica para evitar que las cosas se desmoronen. No confiamos, necesitamos convencernos. Y ahí es donde la fe se empieza a sentir como una cárcel. Porque cuando crees solo para no sufrir, para no equivocarte, para no “caer en desgracia”… en realidad no estás creyendo. Estás obedeciendo al miedo. Estás buscando seguridad, no conexión. La fe vivida desde el miedo se convierte en una especie de trato forzado con el universo: “yo me porto bien, tú me cuidas”. Pero eso no es amor, eso es control disfrazado. La fe que libera no exige perfección, no pide garantías. Es esa voz tranquila que dice “aunque no entienda, estoy en paz”. No porque tengas todo resuelto, sino porque confías en algo más grande —y también en ti. Cuando la fe nace del amor, no te encierra. Te abre. Te acompaña, no te vigila. Te sostiene, no te amenaza.

video_name: Quetzaltenango, en los Altos de Guatemala, existe un lugar que no parece de este mundo: es El Cerro Quemado, un paisaje lunar de rocas volcánicas negras y afiladas. Pero su aterradora apariencia no es un capricho de la naturaleza, la leyenda dice que es la cicatriz de la batalla más importante en la historia del país. Cuentan que este fue el escenario del combate final entre el conquistador Pedro de Alvarado y el héroe maya k'iche', Tecún Umán. #guatemala🇬🇹 #mayas #leyendas #misterio #cerroquemado #xela

bio: Relatos, Leyendas,misterio,conspiraciones

bio: Relatos, Leyendas,misterio,conspiraciones

bio: Relatos, Leyendas,misterio,conspiraciones
video_name: En la selva de Alta Verapaz, Guatemala, existe un lugar donde el mundo de los vivos se encuentra directamente con el infierno: las Cuevas de Candelaria, un gigantesco sistema de cavernas atravesado por un río subterráneo. Para los antiguos mayas Q'eqchi', este no era un lugar para explorar; era un portal sagrado y temido a Xibalbá, su inframundo, el 'lugar del miedo'. #guatemala🇬🇹 #altaverapaz #xibalba #cuevasdecandelaria #mayas #leyendas

bio: Relatos, Leyendas,misterio,conspiraciones
video_name: El Cementerio General de la Ciudad de Guatemala no es solo un lugar de descanso, es una ciudad de los muertos con sus propias leyendas y habitantes nocturnos. Cuando las puertas se cierran y cae la noche sobre sus opulentos mausoleos, se dice que los verdaderos dueños del lugar salen a caminar entre las tumbas. La aparición más famosa y desgarradora es la de 'la niña' #guatemala🇬🇹 #misterio #leyendas #cementeriogeneral #scarystories #paranormal

bio: Relatos, Leyendas,misterio,conspiraciones
video_name: El Panajachel que conocemos hoy, a orillas del majestuoso Lago de Atitlán, no es el original. La leyenda cuenta de un pueblo más antiguo, más cercano al agua, que fue borrado del mapa por la furia del lago, y cuyo corazón, se dice, aún late en las profundidades. Ese primer pueblo tenía una imponente iglesia colonial, y su mayor orgullo era una campana gigantesca, forjada supuestamente con oro macizo. #guatemala🇬🇹 #mistery #misterio #lakeatitlan #panajachel #leyendas #lagodeatitlan

bio: Relatos, Leyendas,misterio,conspiraciones
